      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoI (normalized index of hemolysis, NIH) must be directly mappable to the clinical endpoint with documented sensitivity analysis.",
      "rationale": "NIH is the accepted clinical surrogate for hemolysis. Sensitivity analysis maps NIH to clinical threshold but does not account for patient-specific hematocrit variability. Achieved level 3."
    },
    {
